description: A web developer is a professional who creates and maintains websites and web applications by writing code.
A graphic designer creates visual content to communicate messages through typography, imagery, color, and layout.
A data analyst collects, processes, and performs statistical analyses on large datasets to discover useful information.
An IT support specialist assists users with technical issues and ensures computer systems run smoothly.
A digital marketing specialist develops and implements online marketing strategies to promote products or services.
A content writer produces engaging written content for websites, blogs, and social media platforms.
A mobile app developer designs and builds applications for mobile devices, typically using iOS or Android platforms.
A network administrator manages and maintains computer networks and ensures their optimal performance.
A UI/UX designer focuses on the look and feel of a website or app, ensuring a smooth user experience.
A social media manager creates and manages content across social media platforms to engage an audience and grow followers.
A project manager plans, executes, and closes projects while managing teams, timelines, and resources.
A technical writer creates manuals, guides, and documentation that explain complex technical information clearly.
An SEO specialist improves website visibility in search engine results by optimizing content and structure.
A backend developer builds and maintains the server side of web applications and integrates databases.
A system administrator is responsible for installing, supporting, and maintaining servers and other computer systems.
A DevOps engineer works with software developers and IT staff to manage code releases and improve deployment processes.
A QA tester ensures that software products meet quality standards and function as intended before release.
A front-end developer builds the user interface and client-side features of web applications.
A business analyst analyzes business needs and provides data-driven recommendations for improvement.
A database administrator manages and maintains databases to ensure data availability, security, and performance.
A cybersecurity analyst protects an organizationâ€™s systems and networks from cyber threats and attacks.
